# ── Whitelist approach ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Ignore everything by default, then explicitly re-include only the
# study-note files I generate. Keeps PDFs, other courses, binaries,
# .DS_Store, .claude/, and temp files out of the repo.

*

# allow git to descend into all directories (contents still ignored)
!*/

# repo meta
!.gitignore
!README.md

# generated study notes (matched at any depth → handles spaces in paths)
!**/MBA8105_Notes.md
!**/MBA8105_Notes.html
!**/Leading Change Notes.md
!**/MBA8205_Notes.md
!**/MBA8205_Notes.html
!**/MBA8205_CAT_Study_Guide.md
!**/MBA8205_CAT_Study_Guide.html
!**/MBA8205_CAT_Sample_Questions_Walkthrough.md
!**/MBA8205_CAT_Sample_Questions_Walkthrough.html
!**/build.py

# never include these even if matched above
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
.claude/

# exclude nested repo / other course
mba8104-notes/
mba8104-notes
